{
  "doc_id": "19646",
  "text": "Other investigations of the etiology of Paget's disease have focused on the potential role of chronic paramyxovirus infections contributing to the pathogenesis of the disorder [CITATION_1] . The most impressive animal model of Paget's disease has been generated in transgenic mice by targeting the measles virus nucleocapsid protein and a mutated sequestosome 1 gene into the animals [CITATION_2] . Immunocytochemical studies have shown that Pagetic osteoclasts contain paramyxoviral-like nuclear inclusions that cross-react with antibodies to measles virus, respiratory syncytial virus, and canine distemper virus nucleocapsid antigen [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] [CITATION_5] . Nevertheless, the issue of whether or not viral infections are related to PDB is not resolved [CITATION_6] .",
